        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Find the vertex of $f(x) = 3x^2 - 18x + 14$.",
        "options": [
          "$(3, -13)$",
          "$(-3, 95)$",
          "$(3, 14)$",
          "$(6, -4)$"
        ],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "$x = \\frac{18}{2(3)} = 3$. $f(3) = 27 - 54 + 14 = -13$. Vertex is $(3, -13)$."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "A ball is thrown. Its height is $h(t) = -16t^2 + 80t + 6$. What is the maximum height?",
        "options": [
          "80 feet",
          "106 feet",
          "86 feet",
          "160 feet"
        ],
        "answer": "B",
        "explanation": "$t = \\frac{-80}{2(-16)} = 2.5$. $h(2.5) = -16(6.25) + 80(2.5) + 6 = -100 + 200 + 6 = 106$ feet."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Find the x-intercepts of $f(x) = 6x^2 - x - 15$.",
        "options": [
          "$x = \\frac{5}{3}$ and $x = -\\frac{3}{2}$",
          "$x = \\frac{3}{5}$ and $x = -\\frac{2}{3}$",
          "$x = \\frac{5}{2}$ and $x = -\\frac{1}{3}$",
          "$x = 3$ and $x = -\\frac{5}{2}$"
        ],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "$x = \\frac{1 \\pm \\sqrt{1 + 360}}{12} = \\frac{1 \\pm 19}{12}$. $x = \\frac{20}{12} = \\frac{5}{3}$, $x = \\frac{-18}{12} = -\\frac{3}{2}$."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Find the vertex of $f(x) = -4x^2 + 20x - 9$.",
        "options": [
          "$\\left(\\frac{5}{2}, 16\\right)$",
          "$\\left(\\frac{5}{2}, -9\\right)$",
          "$(5, 16)$",
          "$\\left(-\\frac{5}{2}, -34\\right)$"
        ],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "$x = \\frac{-20}{2(-4)} = \\frac{5}{2}$. $f(\\frac{5}{2}) = -25 + 50 - 9 = 16$. Vertex is $(\\frac{5}{2}, 16)$."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Rearrange to standard form and find the axis of symmetry: $f(x) = (x + 3)(x - 7)$.",
